<section>
<h1>
<span>Appendix D </span>Image Fallback</h1>
<div></div>

<div id="p1">
<p><span>This section is non-normative.</span></p>
</div>
<div id="p2">
<p>User agents that do not support MathML may decide to
render the fallback content provided by the <span>altimg*</span> attributes in some
situations e.g. when they are specified or
under a preference option. In that case, an approximate implementation is to
render the <code>math</code> element as a HTML <code>img</code> element with the
value of <code>altimg</code> as an <code>src</code> attribute, the value of
<code>alttext</code> as an <code>alt</code> attribute, the value of <span>altimg-width</span> as
the CSS <code>width</code> property, the value of <span>altimg-height</span> as
the CSS <code>height</code> property and the value of <span>altimg-valign</span> as
the CSS <span>vertical-align</span> property <cite>[<a href="bib.html#bibx9" title="">HTML5</a>]</cite> <cite>[<a href="bib.html#bibx1" title="">CSS2</a>]</cite>. Here is a
partial implementation using the <span>attr()</span> function of <cite>[<a href="bib.html#bibx3" title="">CSS3Values</a>]</cite>:</p>
<div>
<div><a href="data:text/plain;base64,bWF0aCB7CiAgZGlzcGxheTogaW5saW5lOwp9Cm1hdGhbZGlzcGxheT0iYmxvY2siXSB7CiAgZGlz%0AcGxheTogYmxvY2s7CiAgdGV4dC1hbGlnbjogY2VudGVyOwp9Cm1hdGggewogIGJhY2tncm91bmQt%0AaW1hZ2U6IGF0dHIoYWx0aW1nIHVybCk7CiAgd2lkdGg6IGF0dHIoYWx0aW1nLXdpZHRoIGxlbmd0%0AaCk7CiAgaGVpZ2h0OiBhdHRyKGFsdGltZy1oZWlnaHQgbGVuZ3RoKTsKICB2ZXJ0aWNhbC1hbGln%0AbjogYXR0cihhbHRpbWctdmFsaWduIGxlbmd0aCk7Cn0KbWF0aCA+ICogewogIGRpc3BsYXk6IG5v%0AbmU7Cn0=%0A">⬇</a></div>
<div>
<code>math</code><span> </span><span>{</span>
</div>
<div>
<span>  </span><code>display</code><span>:</span><span> </span><code>inline</code><span>;</span>
</div>
<div>
<span>}</span>
</div>
<div>
<code>math</code><span>[</span><code>display</code><span>="</span><code>block</code><span>"]</span><span> </span><span>{</span>
</div>
<div>
<span>  </span><code>display</code><span>:</span><span> </span><code>block</code><span>;</span>
</div>
<div>
<span>  </span><code>text</code><span>-</span><code>align</code><span>:</span><span> </span><code>center</code><span>;</span>
</div>
<div>
<span>}</span>
</div>
<div>
<code>math</code><span> </span><span>{</span>
</div>
<div>
<span>  </span><code>background</code><span>-</span><code>image</code><span>:</span><span> </span><code>attr</code><span>(</span><code>altimg</code><span> </span><code>url</code><span>);</span>
</div>
<div>
<span>  </span><code>width</code><span>:</span><span> </span><code>attr</code><span>(</span><code>altimg</code><span>-</span><code>width</code><span> </span><code>length</code><span>);</span>
</div>
<div>
<span>  </span><code>height</code><span>:</span><span> </span><code>attr</code><span>(</span><code>altimg</code><span>-</span><code>height</code><span> </span><code>length</code><span>);</span>
</div>
<div>
<span>  </span><code>vertical</code><span>-</span><code>align</code><span>:</span><span> </span><code>attr</code><span>(</span><code>altimg</code><span>-</span><code>valign</code><span> </span><code>length</code><span>);</span>
</div>
<div>
<span>}</span>
</div>
<div>
<code>math</code><span> </span><span>&gt;</span><span> </span><span>*</span><span> </span><span>{</span>
</div>
<div>
<span>  </span><code>display</code><span>:</span><span> </span><code>none</code><span>;</span>
</div>
<div>
<span>}</span>
</div>
</div>
